    h2.bx--type-h4 Visual Hierarchy
    p.bx--type-p
      | Colour is used sparingly to draw attention to important elements. In addition, we use pops of colour to catch the user’s attention encouraging them to take action.

    h2.bx--type-h4.u-pt-5 Accessibility
    p.bx--type-p
      | It’s important that our products meet all web accessibility standards, including the minimum contrast ratios that the WCAG 2.0 specifies for text and background colour combinations. This adherence not only helps colour-blind or low vision users to interact better with LUCA tools, but also improves the usability and readability overall. Choose primary, secondary, and extended colours to ensure sufficient colour contrast between elements.

  .content-block
